main event: A round white and green object was observed descending toward earth at approximately 20 degrees, then leveling off and starting a slight climb. It was visually seen for 20 to 30 seconds.
interesting points: The sighting was attributed to a meteor due to the description, duration, and flight path of the object.
The object was observed by military personnel at Chandler AFS, Minnesota.
The observed object appeared as a falling star but amazed witnesses with its change of altitude and speed.
The weather at the time of the observation was clear with visibility up to 15 miles.
The report indicates that the object may have caused an optical illusion during its slight climb.
